Reverts AEAD-only SCHANNEL hardening by restoring legacy SSL/TLS protocols, re-enabling disabled ciphers, and removing custom cipher suite restrictions from Windows.

Detailed Description

This PowerShell script restores Windows SCHANNEL settings after applying a strict AEAD-only TLS hardening policy by:

Verifying Administrator privileges before making changes.
Restoring protocol support for:
SSL 2.0
SSL 3.0
TLS 1.0
TLS 1.1
TLS 1.2
Re-enabling both Client and Server protocol configurations.
Re-enabling previously disabled ciphers:
Triple DES (3DES)
RC4 128-bit
RC4 56-bit
DES
NULL ciphers
Removing the custom SCHANNEL cipher suite policy stored in:
HKLM\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Cryptography\Configuration\SSL\00010002
Restoring Windows' default cipher suite selection behavior.
Providing progress and completion output.
Recommending a system reboot to ensure SCHANNEL reloads the updated configuration.




[CmdletBinding()]
param ()

begin {

    function Test-IsElevated {
        $id = [System.Security.Principal.WindowsIdentity]::GetCurrent()
        $p = New-Object System.Security.Principal.WindowsPrincipal($id)
        $p.IsInRole([System.Security.Principal.WindowsBuiltInRole]::Administrator)
    }

    if (-not (Test-IsElevated)) {
        Write-Error "Access Denied. Run as Administrator."
        exit 1
    }

    $protocolBase = "HKLM:\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\SecurityProviders\SCHANNEL\Protocols"
    $cipherBase   = "HKLM:\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\SecurityProviders\SCHANNEL\Ciphers"
    $configBase   = "HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Cryptography\Configuration\SSL\00010002"
}

process {

    Write-Output "=== TLS / CIPHER ROLLBACK INITIATED ==="
    Write-Output ""

    # ---------------------------
    # RESTORE TLS PROTOCOLS
    # ---------------------------
    $protocols = @("SSL 2.0","SSL 3.0","TLS 1.0","TLS 1.1","TLS 1.2")

    foreach ($p in $protocols) {

        foreach ($role in @("Server","Client")) {

            $path = "$protocolBase\$p\$role"

            if (!(Test-Path $path)) {
                New-Item $path -Force | Out-Null
            }

            # Restore default Windows behavior (enable where applicable)
            switch ($p) {
                "TLS 1.2" {
                    New-ItemProperty -Path $path -Name "Enabled" -Value 1 -PropertyType DWord -Force | Out-Null
                    New-ItemProperty -Path $path -Name "DisabledByDefault" -Value 0 -PropertyType DWord -Force | Out-Null
                }
                default {
                    New-ItemProperty -Path $path -Name "Enabled" -Value 1 -PropertyType DWord -Force | Out-Null
                    New-ItemProperty -Path $path -Name "DisabledByDefault" -Value 0 -PropertyType DWord -Force | Out-Null
                }
            }
        }

        Write-Output "$p restored to default-enabled state."
    }

    # ---------------------------
    # RE-ENABLE LEGACY CIPHERS
    # ---------------------------
    $legacyCiphers = @(
        "Triple DES 168",
        "RC4 128/128",
        "RC4 56/128",
        "DES 56/56",
        "NULL"
    )

    foreach ($cipher in $legacyCiphers) {

        $path = "$cipherBase\$cipher"

        if (!(Test-Path $path)) {
            New-Item $path -Force | Out-Null
        }

        # Re-enable cipher
        New-ItemProperty -Path $path -Name "Enabled" -Value 1 -PropertyType DWord -Force | Out-Null

        Write-Output "Re-enabled cipher: $cipher"
    }

    # ---------------------------
    # REMOVE CUSTOM AEAD CIPHER SUITE POLICY
    # ---------------------------
    if (Test-Path $configBase) {

        Remove-ItemProperty -Path $configBase -Name "Functions" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue

        Write-Output "Removed custom cipher suite ordering (AEAD-only policy cleared)."
    }

    Write-Output ""
    Write-Output "=== ROLLBACK COMPLETE ==="
    Write-Output "Reboot recommended for full SCHANNEL reload."
}

end {}
